
[1]verify

   VER'IFY, v.t. [L. verus, true, and facio, to make.]

   1. To prove to be true; to confirm.

   This is verified by a number of examples.

   2. To fulfill, as a promise; to confirm the truth of a prediction; to
   show to be true. The predictions of this venerable patriot have been
   verified. Gen. 42. 1Kings 8.

   3. To confirm or establish the authenticity of any thing by examination
   or competent evidence. The first act of the house of representatives is
   to verify their powers, by exhibiting their credentials to a committee
   of the house, or other proper authority.
